This paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for pedestrian detection in the wild. The use of Deep Convolutional Generative Adversarial Networks (DCGANs) and Single Shot Detector (SSD) suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of GANs also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The focus on object detection and smart cities suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of data processing techniques for image completion suggests that the paper may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
